{"word":"Ἰησοῦς","slug":"Ἰησοῦς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>Ἰησοῦς</el>,</b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ gen.\">gen.</a> <b><el>οῦ</el>,</b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ dat.\">dat.</a> <b><el>οῦ</el>,</b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ acc.\">acc.</a> <b><el>οῦν</el>,</b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ voc.\">voc.</a> <b><el>οῦ, <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ὁ\">ὁ</a></el></b> <b>Jesus,</b> Grecized form of the <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Heb.\">Heb.</a> name Joshua/Jeshua (‘God is salvation’/‘God saves’)<b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp> Joshua,</b> successor to Moses <b><a href='B:510 7:45'>Ac 7:45</a>; <a href='B:650 4:8'>Hb 4:8</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp> Jesus,</b> son of Eliezer, ancestor of Jesus <b><a href='B:490 3:29'>Lk 3:29</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>3.</pp> Jesus Christ <a href='B:470 1:1'>Mt 1:1</a></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ al.\">al.</a> <b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>4.</pp> Jesus Barabbas <a href='B:470 27:16'>Mt 27:16f</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>5.</pp> Jesus,</b> called Justus <b><a href='B:580 4:11'>Col 4:11</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:Ἰεχονίας\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἱκανός\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}